%% spill_cold: snapshot clean victims, build+mmap one segment, THEN drop from hot.
%% The snapshot-before-drop ordering means a concurrent reader is never blind.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant E as Controller
    participant S as TapeStore (hot)
    participant O as OocOverlay
    participant D as Disk (mmap segment triple)

    E->>S: spill_cold(victims)
    Note over S: keep only resident AND clean (skip dirty)
    S->>S: snapshot (addr, page) pairs
    S->>O: spill_segment(stem, snapshot)
    O->>D: write .act (key to u64 slot)
    O->>D: write .vals (CtVal01 magic, length-framed Pages)
    O->>D: write .paths (serialize_paths manifest)
    O->>D: mmap the segment, push newest-first
    O-->>S: written count
    S->>S: drop spilled pages from hot PathMap, free RAM
    Note over S: reader sees hot before the drop, overlay after the mmap, never a gap
    S-->>E: count
